Text.SourceString: Oh, hey! I have to say, you’re not what I expected.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, hey! I have to say, you’re not what I expected.

Text.SourceString: Oh no, I didn’t mean it in a bad way.//I heard from the twins who run the inn that a new farmer moved in.//I just thought…you know…//Never mind.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh no, I didn’t mean it in a bad way.//I heard from the twins who run the inn that a new farmer moved in.//I just thought…you know…//Never mind.

Text.SourceString: I’m convinced something’s living in the recycling area next to the community center.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m convinced something’s living in the recycling area next to the community center.

Text.SourceString: I’m not going to waste time trying to convince you. I know what I saw.//<portrait=normal>Some time ago, as I was walking home, I saw <Italic>something</> running really fast toward the bins.//And get this! I asked around the next day, and <NpcName>Pablo</> said he heard the buzzing noise too.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not going to waste time trying to convince you. I know what I saw.//<portrait=normal>Some time ago, as I was walking home, I saw <Italic>something</> running really fast toward the bins.//And get this! I asked around the next day, and <NpcName>Pablo</> said he heard the buzzing noise too.

Text.SourceString: Let me ask you, <PlayerName>$player</>. How can there be a buzzing noise in a place with no machines?
Text.LocalizedString: Let me ask you, <PlayerName>$player</>. How can there be a buzzing noise in a place with no machines?

Text.SourceString: Who’s talking about me? <Italic>I’m</> not talking about me.
Text.LocalizedString: Who’s talking about me? <Italic>I’m</> not talking about me.

Special.SourceString: It can’t. You must have misheard.
Special.LocalizedString: It can’t. You must have misheard.

6.SpecialTag: It can’t. You must have misheard.
6.Question: R1

Text.SourceString: The blacksmith’s place is very close to the recycling center. Hmm… It could be.
Text.LocalizedString: The blacksmith’s place is very close to the recycling center. Hmm… It could be.

Special.SourceString: A machine someplace nearby must have made the noise.
Special.LocalizedString: A machine someplace nearby must have made the noise.

7.SpecialTag: A machine someplace nearby must have made the noise.
7.Question: R2

Text.SourceString: Bam!//<portrait=normal>Your words, not mine.
Text.LocalizedString: Bam!//<portrait=normal>Your words, not mine.

Text.SourceString: I can’t wait for the recycling center to be fixed up.
Text.LocalizedString: I can’t wait for the recycling center to be fixed up.

Text.SourceString: I’m convinced that something’s living in the dumpster next to the community center.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m convinced that something’s living in the dumpster next to the community center.

Text.SourceString: I’m not going to waste my time trying to convince you. I know what I saw.//<portrait=normal>Sometimes ago when I was walking home, I saw <Italic>something</> running really fast towards the dumpster.//And, get this! I asked around the next day, and <NpcName>Pablo</> said he heard the buzzing noise too.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not going to waste my time trying to convince you. I know what I saw.//<portrait=normal>Sometimes ago when I was walking home, I saw <Italic>something</> running really fast towards the dumpster.//And, get this! I asked around the next day, and <NpcName>Pablo</> said he heard the buzzing noise too.

Text.SourceString: When the mayor finally gives approval to put in a community garden, my mom will be ecstatic.
Text.LocalizedString: When the mayor finally gives approval to put in a community garden, my mom will be ecstatic.

Text.SourceString: I have a feeling she’ll be gardening there twenty-four seven.
Text.LocalizedString: I have a feeling she’ll be gardening there twenty-four seven.

Text.SourceString: I like this town. It may not be Pokyo, but it’s home to me.//That’s hard to beat.
Text.LocalizedString: I like this town. It may not be Pokyo, but it’s home to me.//That’s hard to beat.

Text.SourceString: Where else can we get a white-sand beach and a lake, huh?
Text.LocalizedString: Where else can we get a white-sand beach and a lake, huh?

Text.SourceString: Back in the day, my secret hideout was right behind the welcome sign.
Text.LocalizedString: Back in the day, my secret hideout was right behind the welcome sign.

Text.SourceString: Nah, not hiding from people, silly!//<portrait=normal>It was my go-to spot during hide-and-seek games.
Text.LocalizedString: Nah, not hiding from people, silly!//<portrait=normal>It was my go-to spot during hide-and-seek games.

Text.SourceString: No, not much has changed… Starlet has looked like this since I was little.//Every corner holds so many memories.
Text.LocalizedString: No, not much has changed… Starlet has looked like this since I was little.//Every corner holds so many memories.

Text.SourceString: To me, durian tastes exactly like it smells.//<portrait=happy>Prickles aside, it’s simply the best part of Spring.
Text.LocalizedString: To me, durian tastes exactly like it smells.//<portrait=happy>Prickles aside, it’s simply the best part of Spring.

Text.SourceString: Baking a cake is way more complicated than it looks.//For starters, it requires a lot of ingredients.
Text.LocalizedString: Baking a cake is way more complicated than it looks.//For starters, it requires a lot of ingredients.

Text.SourceString: I don't have time to cook just for fun. Running a restaurant is no joke.
Text.LocalizedString: I don't have time to cook just for fun. Running a restaurant is no joke.

Text.SourceString: My mom has a reputation as the best baker around.//If you want to learn a few baking tricks, you should get to know her.
Text.LocalizedString: My mom has a reputation as the best baker around.//If you want to learn a few baking tricks, you should get to know her.

Text.SourceString: I like to knock out my errands before lunch. Helps me focus on work later.
Text.LocalizedString: I like to knock out my errands before lunch. Helps me focus on work later.

Text.SourceString: Something about being at the Tavern makes some people share too much, too soon.//<portrait=sad>Hmm…
Text.LocalizedString: Something about being at the Tavern makes some people share too much, too soon.//<portrait=sad>Hmm…

Text.SourceString: Maybe it's <NPCName>Frank</>'s mixed punch.
Text.LocalizedString: Maybe it's <NPCName>Frank</>'s mixed punch.

Text.SourceString: Got the day off today. Tavern's closed. What's new with you?
Text.LocalizedString: Got the day off today. Tavern's closed. What's new with you?

Text.SourceString: Yeah, we’re open again tomorrow.
Text.LocalizedString: Yeah, we’re open again tomorrow.

Text.SourceString: We get most of our stuff from <NPCName>Sam</>. It's a nice way to back local businesses.
Text.LocalizedString: We get most of our stuff from <NPCName>Sam</>. It's a nice way to back local businesses.

Text.SourceString: I’m turning in early today.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m turning in early today.

Text.SourceString: Eh, just need an early start tomorrow, that's all.
Text.LocalizedString: Eh, just need an early start tomorrow, that's all.

Text.SourceString: We could use more help running the Tavern, but <NpcName>Frank</> is against it.//<portrait=concerned>He thinks it would be throwing money down the drain.
Text.LocalizedString: We could use more help running the Tavern, but <NpcName>Frank</> is against it.//<portrait=concerned>He thinks it would be throwing money down the drain.

Text.SourceString: Getting through to <NPCName>Frank</> about hiring more help is tough. We rarely see things the same way.
Text.LocalizedString: Getting through to <NPCName>Frank</> about hiring more help is tough. We rarely see things the same way.

Text.SourceString: Ah, forget about it. Sorry for venting.
Text.LocalizedString: Ah, forget about it. Sorry for venting.

Text.SourceString: We do our own grocery shopping and cooking.//<portrait=annoyed>It’s very time consuming, if you ask me.
Text.LocalizedString: We do our own grocery shopping and cooking.//<portrait=annoyed>It’s very time consuming, if you ask me.

Text.SourceString: After working at Fishensips for a while, I think selling drinks is where the money’s at.//<portrait=angry>If it were up to me, the Tavern would cut down on serving food and expand the drink menu.
Text.LocalizedString: After working at Fishensips for a while, I think selling drinks is where the money’s at.//<portrait=angry>If it were up to me, the Tavern would cut down on serving food and expand the drink menu.

Text.SourceString: Besides, serving drinks is much easier than serving food.//Less mess, especially with big parties.
Text.LocalizedString: Besides, serving drinks is much easier than serving food.//Less mess, especially with big parties.

Text.SourceString: Do you want to sign up for the live performance?//We only have <NpcName>Theo</> so far. I think he’s all right. People like his energy.
Text.LocalizedString: Do you want to sign up for the live performance?//We only have <NpcName>Theo</> so far. I think he’s all right. People like his energy.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Theo</> gets some quick money, and we get to advertise live music at the Tavern.//<portrait=normal>People are drawn to live music for some reason.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Theo</> gets some quick money, and we get to advertise live music at the Tavern.//<portrait=normal>People are drawn to live music for some reason.

Text.SourceString: The universe is so big, don’t you think? It's kinda arrogant to think it's all here just for us.
Text.LocalizedString: The universe is so big, don’t you think? It's kinda arrogant to think it's all here just for us.

Text.SourceString: The more I read about UFOs, legends, and myths, the more I think we’re not alone in this world.
Text.LocalizedString: The more I read about UFOs, legends, and myths, the more I think we’re not alone in this world.

Text.SourceString: Got work today, but only for half a shift.
Text.LocalizedString: Got work today, but only for half a shift.

Text.SourceString: Hey, how's it going, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: Hey, how's it going, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Frank</> doesn’t mind pulling long shifts. He's into it.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Frank</> doesn’t mind pulling long shifts. He's into it.

Text.SourceString: I always say I’ll go to sleep early, but I end up watching TV until way too late.
Text.LocalizedString: I always say I’ll go to sleep early, but I end up watching TV until way too late.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Frank</> is a good cook. But not much variety, you know?//<portrait=normal>He also has this tendency to substitute ingredients.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Frank</> is a good cook. But not much variety, you know?//<portrait=normal>He also has this tendency to substitute ingredients.

Text.SourceString: Sometimes you don’t really know what you’re getting yourself into.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes you don’t really know what you’re getting yourself into.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Frank</> isn’t the oldest in the family.//<portrait=normal>Aaliyah is… Four siblings total.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Frank</> isn’t the oldest in the family.//<portrait=normal>Aaliyah is… Four siblings total.

Text.SourceString: Nope, I'm not the baby of the family either. Our youngest bro works at a start-up way across the ocean.
Text.LocalizedString: Nope, I'm not the baby of the family either. Our youngest bro works at a start-up way across the ocean.

Text.SourceString: I don’t mind doing the shopping.//That way, <NpcName>Frank</> can focus on cooking.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t mind doing the shopping.//That way, <NpcName>Frank</> can focus on cooking.

Text.SourceString: Finding the right balance between working and taking time for yourself is important.//It helps you refocus on your goals.
Text.LocalizedString: Finding the right balance between working and taking time for yourself is important.//It helps you refocus on your goals.

Text.SourceString: Alice pointed out how it's kinda odd that some flowers bloom at night. Like, post-sunset. Don't they need sunshine?
Text.LocalizedString: Alice pointed out how it's kinda odd that some flowers bloom at night. Like, post-sunset. Don't they need sunshine?

Text.SourceString: Guess not, huh... Interesting.
Text.LocalizedString: Guess not, huh... Interesting.

Text.SourceString: Strongest memory?//<portrait=happy>Tough to pick, but the pranks stand out. You learn a new one every day when you've got a lot of siblings, trust me!
Text.LocalizedString: Strongest memory?//<portrait=happy>Tough to pick, but the pranks stand out. You learn a new one every day when you've got a lot of siblings, trust me!

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Frank</> was born in Summer, maybe that's why he's always so chipper... Is that a thing?
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Frank</> was born in Summer, maybe that's why he's always so chipper... Is that a thing?

Text.SourceString: With three siblings, every day felt like a birthday bash at our place.
Text.LocalizedString: With three siblings, every day felt like a birthday bash at our place.

Text.SourceString: One of these days, I’m gonna miss somebody’s birthday…//<portrait=sad>I just know it.//<portrait=concerned>And that somebody will get upset because they remembered mine…//These social norms are just so hard to keep track of.
Text.LocalizedString: One of these days, I’m gonna miss somebody’s birthday…//<portrait=sad>I just know it.//<portrait=concerned>And that somebody will get upset because they remembered mine…//These social norms are just so hard to keep track of.

Text.SourceString: It's not like I mean to forget... Keeping up with birthdays can be pretty overwhelming.
Text.LocalizedString: It's not like I mean to forget... Keeping up with birthdays can be pretty overwhelming.

Text.SourceString: Having three siblings taught me there’s no such thing as personal space.
Text.LocalizedString: Having three siblings taught me there’s no such thing as personal space.

Text.SourceString: Gah. I miss <NpcName>Eddy</>.
Text.LocalizedString: Gah. I miss <NpcName>Eddy</>.

Text.SourceString: When I was growing up, Mama and Dad assigned each of us a roommate.//<portrait=happy>I got <NPCName>Frank</>, and our sis was stuck with baby bro <NPCName>Eddy</>.
Text.LocalizedString: When I was growing up, Mama and Dad assigned each of us a roommate.//<portrait=happy>I got <NPCName>Frank</>, and our sis was stuck with baby bro <NPCName>Eddy</>.

Text.SourceString: I hope it won’t rain tomorrow. I need to visit the vineyard to pick up some wine…//<portrait=normal>The Tavern is dangerously low.
Text.LocalizedString: I hope it won’t rain tomorrow. I need to visit the vineyard to pick up some wine…//<portrait=normal>The Tavern is dangerously low.

Text.SourceString: I’m not like my kitchen-warrior brother, <NpcName>Frank</>. I’m afraid I can only cook sunny-side up.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not like my kitchen-warrior brother, <NpcName>Frank</>. I’m afraid I can only cook sunny-side up.

Text.SourceString: Do you think that’s good enough?
Text.LocalizedString: Do you think that’s good enough?

Text.SourceString: Please, don't order the 'mixed punch' - it's basically <NPCName>Frank</>'s failed experiment.//Save your stomach the trouble.
Text.LocalizedString: Please, don't order the 'mixed punch' - it's basically <NPCName>Frank</>'s failed experiment.//Save your stomach the trouble.

Text.SourceString: I grew up eating <NpcName>Frank’s</> experimental food, probably why I'm picky about food now.
Text.LocalizedString: I grew up eating <NpcName>Frank’s</> experimental food, probably why I'm picky about food now.

Text.SourceString: My dad used to say, “To test a marriage, you should either open a restaurant or have a bunch of kids.”
Text.LocalizedString: My dad used to say, “To test a marriage, you should either open a restaurant or have a bunch of kids.”

Text.SourceString: My parents did both, and they survived! I know he was joking, but I think it’s accurate.
Text.LocalizedString: My parents did both, and they survived! I know he was joking, but I think it’s accurate.

Text.SourceString: Well, what else am I going to do on my day off?
Text.LocalizedString: Well, what else am I going to do on my day off?

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Frank</> and I can’t take the weekend off. That’s when the Tavern is the busiest.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Frank</> and I can’t take the weekend off. That’s when the Tavern is the busiest.

Text.SourceString: The Tavern could charge a premium for drinks and meals, don’t you think? We use only the best ingredients.
Text.LocalizedString: The Tavern could charge a premium for drinks and meals, don’t you think? We use only the best ingredients.

Text.SourceString: I don't think a 20% price hike would drive people away. But we’re too afraid to risk it, I guess.
Text.LocalizedString: I don't think a 20% price hike would drive people away. But we’re too afraid to risk it, I guess.

Text.SourceString: One thing I don’t miss about Pokyo, though, is the constant blaring of car horns.
Text.LocalizedString: One thing I don’t miss about Pokyo, though, is the constant blaring of car horns.

Text.SourceString: I lost a lot of sleep because of that, which inevitably affected my mood.
Text.LocalizedString: I lost a lot of sleep because of that, which inevitably affected my mood.

Text.SourceString: I'm looking forward to taking mom to the beach next week.
Text.LocalizedString: I'm looking forward to taking mom to the beach next week.

Text.SourceString: Had a great time this week just strolling around town and catching up with her.
Text.LocalizedString: Had a great time this week just strolling around town and catching up with her.

Text.SourceString: Best memory with Mama? Ah, that's a tough one. So many great beach times with her, can't pick just one.
Text.LocalizedString: Best memory with Mama? Ah, that's a tough one. So many great beach times with her, can't pick just one.

Text.SourceString: There are so many interesting Spring crops. I don’t understand why <NPCName>Frank</> won’t introduce a seasonal menu to take advantage of them.
Text.LocalizedString: There are so many interesting Spring crops. I don’t understand why <NPCName>Frank</> won’t introduce a seasonal menu to take advantage of them.

Text.SourceString: Honestly, at this point, I’m just counting down the days until Summer.
Text.LocalizedString: Honestly, at this point, I’m just counting down the days until Summer.

Text.SourceString: If Mama can cook seasonal food, why can’t <NPCName>Frank</>? And why can’t we serve it at the Tavern?//<portrait=normal>Now’s the perfect time for a seasonal menu.
Text.LocalizedString: If Mama can cook seasonal food, why can’t <NPCName>Frank</>? And why can’t we serve it at the Tavern?//<portrait=normal>Now’s the perfect time for a seasonal menu.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Frank</> and I are getting ready for the Cherry Blossom Festival.//Mama and Dad used to help make the hot pot, but we took over, even before Dad passed away.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Frank</> and I are getting ready for the Cherry Blossom Festival.//Mama and Dad used to help make the hot pot, but we took over, even before Dad passed away.

Text.SourceString: The trees back in Pokyo never looked this good in Spring. So glad I moved back after graduation.
Text.LocalizedString: The trees back in Pokyo never looked this good in Spring. So glad I moved back after graduation.

Text.SourceString: I’m gathering all the ingredients for the hot pot.//<portrait=happy>Well, other than the ones the townsfolk are bringing, of course.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m gathering all the ingredients for the hot pot.//<portrait=happy>Well, other than the ones the townsfolk are bringing, of course.

Text.SourceString: Finally, it’s Summer!//Have you planted your Summer crops yet?
Text.LocalizedString: Finally, it’s Summer!//Have you planted your Summer crops yet?

Text.SourceString: With the temperature rising, I think I’ll take Mama to Hillside for morning walks… Too much beach isn’t good for her.
Text.LocalizedString: With the temperature rising, I think I’ll take Mama to Hillside for morning walks… Too much beach isn’t good for her.

Text.SourceString: Our air conditioner broke the other day. Thankfully, <NPCName>Pablo</> fixed it.//Some of the wiring was moldy, apparently. Good thing it wasn’t anything worse, like rats.
Text.LocalizedString: Our air conditioner broke the other day. Thankfully, <NPCName>Pablo</> fixed it.//Some of the wiring was moldy, apparently. Good thing it wasn’t anything worse, like rats.

Text.SourceString: I was thinking maybe we could open a booth at one of the festivals, like the annual beach cleanup. Perfect, right?//We could sell cold drinks, homemade sweets… I don’t know. People swim, they get hungry. Simple logic to me.//But <NPCName>Frank</> won’t even give it a chance. Not enough staff.
Text.LocalizedString: I was thinking maybe we could open a booth at one of the festivals, like the annual beach cleanup. Perfect, right?//We could sell cold drinks, homemade sweets… I don’t know. People swim, they get hungry. Simple logic to me.//But <NPCName>Frank</> won’t even give it a chance. Not enough staff.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Alice</> thinks there’s intelligent life in the sky, but my money is on under the water.//<portrait=normal>Did you know we’ve explored less than 20 percent of the ocean?//<portrait=surprised>There’s gotta be merfolk or something living in the other 80 percent!
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Alice</> thinks there’s intelligent life in the sky, but my money is on under the water.//<portrait=normal>Did you know we’ve explored less than 20 percent of the ocean?//<portrait=surprised>There’s gotta be merfolk or something living in the other 80 percent!

Text.SourceString: I need to tell Mama to wear her hat. She can’t be walking around in this Summer heat without one.//I’m worried she might get light-headed at the lake, and…//I don’t even wanna think about it.
Text.LocalizedString: I need to tell Mama to wear her hat. She can’t be walking around in this Summer heat without one.//I’m worried she might get light-headed at the lake, and…//I don’t even wanna think about it.

Text.SourceString: Sometimes <NPCName>Alice</> invites me to go to the forest to look for cryptids, but I’d rather search in the ocean or around the beach.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes <NPCName>Alice</> invites me to go to the forest to look for cryptids, but I’d rather search in the ocean or around the beach.

Text.SourceString: <PlayerName>$player</>! I saw something swimming in the distance the other day, and it was shimmering. It must have been a merperson! Wait until I tell <NPCName>Alice</> about this.//Or it could’ve been <Italic>another</> seal, like that one time…
Text.LocalizedString: <PlayerName>$player</>! I saw something swimming in the distance the other day, and it was shimmering. It must have been a merperson! Wait until I tell <NPCName>Alice</> about this.//Or it could’ve been <Italic>another</> seal, like that one time…

Text.SourceString: The tide can get pretty high in Summer, but so far, it hasn’t ever reached the Tavern.//Thank goodness, right? That sounds expensive to fix.
Text.LocalizedString: The tide can get pretty high in Summer, but so far, it hasn’t ever reached the Tavern.//Thank goodness, right? That sounds expensive to fix.

Text.SourceString: You know, there’s a folk legend that says the daisy patches in Summer are places where they’ve buried a pure and innocent child who died.
Text.LocalizedString: You know, there’s a folk legend that says the daisy patches in Summer are places where they’ve buried a pure and innocent child who died.

Text.SourceString: But another story says they’re where the fairies sleep.//I like the fairy story better, honestly.
Text.LocalizedString: But another story says they’re where the fairies sleep.//I like the fairy story better, honestly.

Text.SourceString: Such a bummer that Summer is over. But I guess it means I can focus more on the Tavern.
Text.LocalizedString: Such a bummer that Summer is over. But I guess it means I can focus more on the Tavern.

Text.SourceString: The beach is still pretty fun in Fall, but not as much as it is in Summer.
Text.LocalizedString: The beach is still pretty fun in Fall, but not as much as it is in Summer.

Text.SourceString: Our family wasn’t as busy for the Harvest Festival… Yeah, we helped out.//But we pretty much hosted the Cherry Blossom Festival.
Text.LocalizedString: Our family wasn’t as busy for the Harvest Festival… Yeah, we helped out.//But we pretty much hosted the Cherry Blossom Festival.

Text.SourceString: I think Fall is the best season for eating roasted mushrooms. It’s the best season for making them too!//They’re sprouting in the wild. You can hunt for them in the forest.
Text.LocalizedString: I think Fall is the best season for eating roasted mushrooms. It’s the best season for making them too!//They’re sprouting in the wild. You can hunt for them in the forest.

Text.SourceString: I don’t know why anyone would eat mushrooms raw. Ew.//<portrait=happy>Now roasted, that’s the way to go.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t know why anyone would eat mushrooms raw. Ew.//<portrait=happy>Now roasted, that’s the way to go.

Text.SourceString: I managed to find tons of mushrooms the other day! Now I just need to roast them all.//Not a big fan of cleaning them, though. It’s a lot of work.//The dirt just doesn’t seem to come off.
Text.LocalizedString: I managed to find tons of mushrooms the other day! Now I just need to roast them all.//Not a big fan of cleaning them, though. It’s a lot of work.//The dirt just doesn’t seem to come off.

Text.SourceString: Are you ready for the New Year’s Eve Festival? I know I am.//<portrait=happy>Yes, I know this is still the first week of Winter, but you can never prepare too early!
Text.LocalizedString: Are you ready for the New Year’s Eve Festival? I know I am.//<portrait=happy>Yes, I know this is still the first week of Winter, but you can never prepare too early!

Text.SourceString: I can’t wait to eat all the good food at the New Year’s Eve Festival.//The Duckorns, <NPCName>Luke’s</> family, usually have it catered by fancy Pokyo restaurants.//They had garlic ice cream a few years ago… It was weird but delicious.
Text.LocalizedString: I can’t wait to eat all the good food at the New Year’s Eve Festival.//The Duckorns, <NPCName>Luke’s</> family, usually have it catered by fancy Pokyo restaurants.//They had garlic ice cream a few years ago… It was weird but delicious.

Text.SourceString: Gotta say I’m not a big fan of the cold, but then again, who is, right?//Wait… Are you?
Text.LocalizedString: Gotta say I’m not a big fan of the cold, but then again, who is, right?//Wait… Are you?

Text.SourceString: I have a video camera in my room that I usually leave on during Winter nights to record the sky.//One time, when I was about <NPCName>Archie’s</> age, I stayed up watching TV. It was pretty late, and I saw something flying in the sky – a sleigh.//I know, I know. But I know what I saw, so I’m trying to catch it on video.
Text.LocalizedString: I have a video camera in my room that I usually leave on during Winter nights to record the sky.//One time, when I was about <NPCName>Archie’s</> age, I stayed up watching TV. It was pretty late, and I saw something flying in the sky – a sleigh.//I know, I know. But I know what I saw, so I’m trying to catch it on video.

Text.SourceString: If it were warmer, I think I’d spend more time outside, but as it is?//<portrait=normal>I think I’ll just do the paperwork for the Tavern.//Somebody’s gotta do the accounting, and it isn’t gonna be my big bro.
Text.LocalizedString: If it were warmer, I think I’d spend more time outside, but as it is?//<portrait=normal>I think I’ll just do the paperwork for the Tavern.//Somebody’s gotta do the accounting, and it isn’t gonna be my big bro.

Text.SourceString: Restocking supplies and doing paperwork is much better than being outside in the cold.
Text.LocalizedString: Restocking supplies and doing paperwork is much better than being outside in the cold.

Text.SourceString: If you have time, try some of our food and drinks. They’re the islanders’ favorites.
Text.LocalizedString: If you have time, try some of our food and drinks. They’re the islanders’ favorites.

Text.SourceString: They also make great gifts.//It’s an easy way to win people over, you know?
Text.LocalizedString: They also make great gifts.//It’s an easy way to win people over, you know?

Text.SourceString: A couple of very well-dressed people came here last year and started taking pictures. But they weren’t acting like tourists, you see.
Text.LocalizedString: A couple of very well-dressed people came here last year and started taking pictures. But they weren’t acting like tourists, you see.

Text.SourceString: They mostly kept to themselves, and they each had a little yellow brooch on their jacket. I guess they were Pufferfish employees, surveying the area.
Text.LocalizedString: They mostly kept to themselves, and they each had a little yellow brooch on their jacket. I guess they were Pufferfish employees, surveying the area.

Text.SourceString: *humming*
Text.LocalizedString: *humming*

Text.SourceString: We’ll be at the Cherry Blossom Festival on Wednesday. <NPCName>Frank</> will be grilling all day, so we should probably arrive a bit early to get things ready.
Text.LocalizedString: We’ll be at the Cherry Blossom Festival on Wednesday. <NPCName>Frank</> will be grilling all day, so we should probably arrive a bit early to get things ready.

Text.SourceString: They should at least consider having another potluck this Summer.
Text.LocalizedString: They should at least consider having another potluck this Summer.

Text.SourceString: Oh… Maybe we can have a potluck in Fall and Winter too…//<portrait=normal>When people bring their favorite dish for the community to enjoy, the gathering is more meaningful. It has that big-family feel.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh… Maybe we can have a potluck in Fall and Winter too…//<portrait=normal>When people bring their favorite dish for the community to enjoy, the gathering is more meaningful. It has that big-family feel.

Text.SourceString: Tomorrow is the first day of Summer.//<portrait=normal>Get ready, <PlayerName>$player</>. It’s going to get really hot.
Text.LocalizedString: Tomorrow is the first day of Summer.//<portrait=normal>Get ready, <PlayerName>$player</>. It’s going to get really hot.

Text.SourceString: It’s only the beginning of Spring, but I already can’t wait to spend my Summer soaking up some sun at the beach.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s only the beginning of Spring, but I already can’t wait to spend my Summer soaking up some sun at the beach.

Text.SourceString: Another exciting thing about Summer is merfolk supposedly come out in the warmer weather…//<portrait=happy>Makes no sense whatsoever.//<portrait=normal>Also, impossible to prove.
Text.LocalizedString: Another exciting thing about Summer is merfolk supposedly come out in the warmer weather…//<portrait=happy>Makes no sense whatsoever.//<portrait=normal>Also, impossible to prove.

Text.SourceString: Are you excited for your first Summer here, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: Are you excited for your first Summer here, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: I’m taking a bit of a break today, just trying to spend time outdoors.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m taking a bit of a break today, just trying to spend time outdoors.

Text.SourceString: It’s Summer, after all. Right?
Text.LocalizedString: It’s Summer, after all. Right?

Text.SourceString: You can learn a thing or two from your neighbors.//You might pick up a simple recipe to try out or even learn how to craft items for your farm.
Text.LocalizedString: You can learn a thing or two from your neighbors.//You might pick up a simple recipe to try out or even learn how to craft items for your farm.

Text.SourceString: Get to know them, and they might share their knowledge with you.
Text.LocalizedString: Get to know them, and they might share their knowledge with you.

Text.SourceString: I picked up some coconuts from the beach the other day. They can be a quick hydration solution…//<portrait=surprised>Bah!//<portrait=blushing>That was a mouthful to say.
Text.LocalizedString: I picked up some coconuts from the beach the other day. They can be a quick hydration solution…//<portrait=surprised>Bah!//<portrait=blushing>That was a mouthful to say.

Text.SourceString: The wind is getting colder. I think Fall is finally here.
Text.LocalizedString: The wind is getting colder. I think Fall is finally here.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Frank</> needs more help in Fall, so I usually work extra shifts on Sundays.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Frank</> needs more help in Fall, so I usually work extra shifts on Sundays.

Text.SourceString: If I don’t keep an eye on my mom, who will?
Text.LocalizedString: If I don’t keep an eye on my mom, who will?

Text.SourceString: My siblings all left the nest already. I’m all she’s got left.
Text.LocalizedString: My siblings all left the nest already. I’m all she’s got left.

Text.SourceString: Taking a break from the farm, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: Taking a break from the farm, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: I’ve been baking a lot more lately, but nothing’s turned out good… Bummer!
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve been baking a lot more lately, but nothing’s turned out good… Bummer!

Text.SourceString: I don’t have a sweet tooth, so I think it’s just the cold weather getting to me. You know, having a bigger appetite and all.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t have a sweet tooth, so I think it’s just the cold weather getting to me. You know, having a bigger appetite and all.

Text.SourceString: It’s truffle season. I’m keeping an eye out in case I spot one in the wild.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s truffle season. I’m keeping an eye out in case I spot one in the wild.

Text.SourceString: They’re rare, though.
Text.LocalizedString: They’re rare, though.

Text.SourceString: Mama and I used to spend my birthday hunting for truffles and Winter vegetables in the forest. Then at night, she’d cook them up as a side dish for ramen.
Text.LocalizedString: Mama and I used to spend my birthday hunting for truffles and Winter vegetables in the forest. Then at night, she’d cook them up as a side dish for ramen.

Text.SourceString: We spent way too much money on a new heater for the Tavern.
Text.LocalizedString: We spent way too much money on a new heater for the Tavern.

Text.SourceString: The old one was fine. But <NPCName>Frank</> thought it was important to get a new heater in case the old one broke in the middle of Winter.
Text.LocalizedString: The old one was fine. But <NPCName>Frank</> thought it was important to get a new heater in case the old one broke in the middle of Winter.

Text.SourceString: I haven’t complained once about how cold it is this Winter.//Go, me!
Text.LocalizedString: I haven’t complained once about how cold it is this Winter.//Go, me!

Text.SourceString: Nothing beats the feeling of the warm Spring sun after a cold Winter.
Text.LocalizedString: Nothing beats the feeling of the warm Spring sun after a cold Winter.

Text.SourceString: The weather is putting people in a good mood.
Text.LocalizedString: The weather is putting people in a good mood.

Text.SourceString: Spring rains are my favorite. They might make the farm a bit muddy, but seeing everything refreshed and sparkling afterwards, it's worth it.
Text.LocalizedString: Spring rains are my favorite. They might make the farm a bit muddy, but seeing everything refreshed and sparkling afterwards, it's worth it.

Text.SourceString: You must not have a lot of watering to do today, eh?
Text.LocalizedString: You must not have a lot of watering to do today, eh?

Text.SourceString: I hope there isn’t a leak in the community center.
Text.LocalizedString: I hope there isn’t a leak in the community center.

Text.SourceString: I’m going to check on the library when the rain settles down.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m going to check on the library when the rain settles down.

Text.SourceString: Something warm sounds good right now.
Text.LocalizedString: Something warm sounds good right now.

Text.SourceString: Is it actually darker than usual outside, or am I losing my mind?
Text.LocalizedString: Is it actually darker than usual outside, or am I losing my mind?

Text.SourceString: The Tavern gets extra muddy when it rains.//<portrait=annoyed>People just don’t bother wiping their feet.
Text.LocalizedString: The Tavern gets extra muddy when it rains.//<portrait=annoyed>People just don’t bother wiping their feet.

Text.SourceString: Is it actually darker than usual outside, or am I losing my mind?
Text.LocalizedString: Is it actually darker than usual outside, or am I losing my mind?

Text.SourceString: The tavern gets extra muddy when it rains.//<portrait=annoyed>People just don’t bother wiping their feet.
Text.LocalizedString: The tavern gets extra muddy when it rains.//<portrait=annoyed>People just don’t bother wiping their feet.

Text.SourceString: Oh, um…be safe out there, <PlayerName>$player</>.//The storm is really bad today.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, um…be safe out there, <PlayerName>$player</>.//The storm is really bad today.

Text.SourceString: I don’t know if it’s safe to walk around in this weather.//<portrait=sad>What am I thinking?
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t know if it’s safe to walk around in this weather.//<portrait=sad>What am I thinking?

Text.SourceString: Your cheeks are getting red. You need to warm up, <PlayerName>$player</>.
Text.LocalizedString: Your cheeks are getting red. You need to warm up, <PlayerName>$player</>.

Text.SourceString: When I was in elementary school, our sister would boil potatoes in the morning to put in our coat pockets.
Text.LocalizedString: When I was in elementary school, our sister would boil potatoes in the morning to put in our coat pockets.

Text.SourceString: The potatoes were to keep our hands warm.//Then we would eat them when we got to school.
Text.LocalizedString: The potatoes were to keep our hands warm.//Then we would eat them when we got to school.

Text.SourceString: I walked past your farm on my way to <NpcName>Ben’s</> the other day.//It looked so beautiful covered in snow.
Text.LocalizedString: I walked past your farm on my way to <NpcName>Ben’s</> the other day.//It looked so beautiful covered in snow.

Text.SourceString: I hope you don’t mind if I stop by your place sometime.
Text.LocalizedString: I hope you don’t mind if I stop by your place sometime.

Text.SourceString: I keep telling Mama to see <NpcName>Yuri</> for her hip pain, but she keeps ignoring it.//<portrait=concerned>She told me it’s just old age.
Text.LocalizedString: I keep telling Mama to see <NpcName>Yuri</> for her hip pain, but she keeps ignoring it.//<portrait=concerned>She told me it’s just old age.

Text.SourceString: Even if it’s just normal joint pain, why not get a professional opinion, right?
Text.LocalizedString: Even if it’s just normal joint pain, why not get a professional opinion, right?

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Alice</> likes to keep warm by staying active, but not me.//I’d rather bundle up in bed.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Alice</> likes to keep warm by staying active, but not me.//I’d rather bundle up in bed.

Text.SourceString: I walked past your farm on my way to <NpcName>Ben</>’s the other day.//It looked so beautiful covered in snow.
Text.LocalizedString: I walked past your farm on my way to <NpcName>Ben</>’s the other day.//It looked so beautiful covered in snow.

Text.SourceString: I hope you don’t mind if I stop by your place sometimes.
Text.LocalizedString: I hope you don’t mind if I stop by your place sometimes.

Text.SourceString: I walked past your farm on my way to <NpcName>Ben</>’s the other day.//It looked so beautiful covered in snow.
Text.LocalizedString: I walked past your farm on my way to <NpcName>Ben</>’s the other day.//It looked so beautiful covered in snow.

Text.SourceString: I hope you don’t mind if I stop by your place sometimes.
Text.LocalizedString: I hope you don’t mind if I stop by your place sometimes.

Text.SourceString: I can’t bear the thought of moving out and leaving my mom alone.
Text.LocalizedString: I can’t bear the thought of moving out and leaving my mom alone.

Text.SourceString: I know she says she’s fine, but I don’t want to see her all alone in this big building.
Text.LocalizedString: I know she says she’s fine, but I don’t want to see her all alone in this big building.

Text.SourceString: I bumped my head trying to clean the cabinet this morning.
Text.LocalizedString: I bumped my head trying to clean the cabinet this morning.

Text.SourceString: It still hurts.
Text.LocalizedString: It still hurts.

Text.SourceString: Hmm… It feels incredibly humid today!//<portrait=annoyed>I hate the sticky feeling in the Summer.//<portrait=concerned>The heat is nice sometimes, but in this heat, just being outside can be tiring. Even if I’m doing nothing.
Text.LocalizedString: Hmm… It feels incredibly humid today!//<portrait=annoyed>I hate the sticky feeling in the Summer.//<portrait=concerned>The heat is nice sometimes, but in this heat, just being outside can be tiring. Even if I’m doing nothing.

Text.SourceString: Summer nights are great, though!
Text.LocalizedString: Summer nights are great, though!

Text.SourceString: Good morning, <PlayerName>$player</>.//<portrait=normal>You’re out early today. Running errands?
Text.LocalizedString: Good morning, <PlayerName>$player</>.//<portrait=normal>You’re out early today. Running errands?

Text.SourceString: I make a habit of checking the weather channel every morning before heading out.//You know, in case it might rain or something.
Text.LocalizedString: I make a habit of checking the weather channel every morning before heading out.//You know, in case it might rain or something.

Text.SourceString: I’ll just have a small breakfast here before my doctor’s appointment at noon.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ll just have a small breakfast here before my doctor’s appointment at noon.

Text.SourceString: Yeah, I’m okay, thanks for asking. //<portrait=normal>Just going for a checkup.
Text.LocalizedString: Yeah, I’m okay, thanks for asking. //<portrait=normal>Just going for a checkup.

Text.SourceString: I think I just caught one of my brother’s cats trying to sneak in here.
Text.LocalizedString: I think I just caught one of my brother’s cats trying to sneak in here.

Text.SourceString: I’ll check on the cats later before I go to work.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ll check on the cats later before I go to work.

Text.SourceString: *mumbling* Oil, two loaves of bread…
Text.LocalizedString: *mumbling* Oil, two loaves of bread…

Text.SourceString: No matter how often you sweep the Tavern’s balcony, it’s impossible to keep it clean this time of year.//The leaves are falling constantly.
Text.LocalizedString: No matter how often you sweep the Tavern’s balcony, it’s impossible to keep it clean this time of year.//The leaves are falling constantly.

Text.SourceString: Your farm is just over the creek, right?
Text.LocalizedString: Your farm is just over the creek, right?

Text.SourceString: When it’s not raining, I try to come here to watch the sunset.
Text.LocalizedString: When it’s not raining, I try to come here to watch the sunset.

Text.SourceString: You can watch the sunset every day from your farm, yeah?//<portrait=happy>So lucky!
Text.LocalizedString: You can watch the sunset every day from your farm, yeah?//<portrait=happy>So lucky!

Text.SourceString: We live in the middle of town. Ugh…//<portrait=normal>I wish the Tavern was closer to the beach.//I’m pretty sure it would bring us more business, too.
Text.LocalizedString: We live in the middle of town. Ugh…//<portrait=normal>I wish the Tavern was closer to the beach.//I’m pretty sure it would bring us more business, too.

Text.SourceString: Have you been inside the lighthouse, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: Have you been inside the lighthouse, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: Ah, I can’t look down the cliff.
Text.LocalizedString: Ah, I can’t look down the cliff.

Text.SourceString: It’s giving me a headache…//My head is pounding.//Nope!
Text.LocalizedString: It’s giving me a headache…//My head is pounding.//Nope!

Text.SourceString: I might grow my hair out after this.
Text.LocalizedString: I might grow my hair out after this.

Text.SourceString: I might stay here a little longer to cool off.
Text.LocalizedString: I might stay here a little longer to cool off.

Text.SourceString: It’s so hot outside.//I’m glad <NpcName>Sam</> has his air conditioner on full blast.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s so hot outside.//I’m glad <NpcName>Sam</> has his air conditioner on full blast.

Text.SourceString: Oh, bees! Why is it so cold in here?!//<portrait=surprised>With the snow and all, you would think <NpcName>Sam</> would turn down the coolers a bit.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, bees! Why is it so cold in here?!//<portrait=surprised>With the snow and all, you would think <NpcName>Sam</> would turn down the coolers a bit.

Text.SourceString: *shivers* I’ve got to get my shopping done fast. It’s too cold in here.//I can’t think.
Text.LocalizedString: *shivers* I’ve got to get my shopping done fast. It’s too cold in here.//I can’t think.

Text.SourceString: Some people say there are humanoid creatures living deep in the forest... Legend has it they're trapped by an evil spirit and can't get back home.
Text.LocalizedString: Some people say there are humanoid creatures living deep in the forest... Legend has it they're trapped by an evil spirit and can't get back home.

Text.SourceString: Yeah, I don't know! I like reading about legends and stuff, but can't find many books on it.//<portrait=normal>One mentioned them as Giants... Tiny Giants, actually.
Text.LocalizedString: Yeah, I don't know! I like reading about legends and stuff, but can't find many books on it.//<portrait=normal>One mentioned them as Giants... Tiny Giants, actually.

Text.SourceString: The most interesting legends? Hmm… It’s hard to pick.//The crying rock is an interesting one.
Text.LocalizedString: The most interesting legends? Hmm… It’s hard to pick.//The crying rock is an interesting one.

Text.SourceString: Do I believe them? That’s another story… It would be on a case-by-case basis.//<portrait=normal>I don’t believe everything I read…//Most of them are just for fun.
Text.LocalizedString: Do I believe them? That’s another story… It would be on a case-by-case basis.//<portrait=normal>I don’t believe everything I read…//Most of them are just for fun.

Text.SourceString: The house is filled with <NpcName>Aaliyah’s</> trophies. Don’t bother looking for mine. Never contributed to the collection.//She’s been collecting rewards like Dokepon cards since we were little!
Text.LocalizedString: The house is filled with <NpcName>Aaliyah’s</> trophies. Don’t bother looking for mine. Never contributed to the collection.//She’s been collecting rewards like Dokepon cards since we were little!

Text.SourceString: With all the coconuts around the island free to harvest, I wonder if we should start selling coconut drinks at Fishensips.//It’s a great way to hydrate, and the base cost is dirt cheap.
Text.LocalizedString: With all the coconuts around the island free to harvest, I wonder if we should start selling coconut drinks at Fishensips.//It’s a great way to hydrate, and the base cost is dirt cheap.

Text.SourceString: But the Beach Shack is already selling coconut drinks…hmm. Not sure if it’s the right thing to do.//I should talk to my sister about it, get some advice. <NpcName>Aaliyah</> is good with numbers.
Text.LocalizedString: But the Beach Shack is already selling coconut drinks…hmm. Not sure if it’s the right thing to do.//I should talk to my sister about it, get some advice. <NpcName>Aaliyah</> is good with numbers.

Text.SourceString: With all the coconuts around the island free to harvest, I wonder if we should start selling coconut drinks at Fishensips.//It’s a great way to hydrate and the base cost is dirt cheap.
Text.LocalizedString: With all the coconuts around the island free to harvest, I wonder if we should start selling coconut drinks at Fishensips.//It’s a great way to hydrate and the base cost is dirt cheap.

Text.SourceString: But Beach Shack is already selling coconut drinks…hmm…not sure if that’s the right thing to do.//I should talk to my sister about it…get some advice. <NpcName>Aaliyah</> is good with numbers.
Text.LocalizedString: But Beach Shack is already selling coconut drinks…hmm…not sure if that’s the right thing to do.//I should talk to my sister about it…get some advice. <NpcName>Aaliyah</> is good with numbers.

Text.SourceString: I know Winter has just started, but let me get this off my chest.//The moment Summer is here, I pledge to never leave the beach.
Text.LocalizedString: I know Winter has just started, but let me get this off my chest.//The moment Summer is here, I pledge to never leave the beach.

Text.SourceString: I’ll camp there and enjoy every minute of the salty Summer breeze.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ll camp there and enjoy every minute of the salty Summer breeze.

Text.SourceString: It’s kind of bittersweet to see the cats now that Dad has passed away.//<portrait=sad>It brings back a lot of memories.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s kind of bittersweet to see the cats now that Dad has passed away.//<portrait=sad>It brings back a lot of memories.

Text.SourceString: I’m not sure how old the cats are, <NPCName>Peanut</> and <NPCName>Butter</>… But they’ve been around since Dad was here.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not sure how old the cats are, <NPCName>Peanut</> and <NPCName>Butter</>… But they’ve been around since Dad was here.

Text.SourceString: I’ve always been close to my mom. I wish I could have had a bit more time with Dad, but it’s no use mourning now.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve always been close to my mom. I wish I could have had a bit more time with Dad, but it’s no use mourning now.

Text.SourceString: Dad had a happy and long life. I don’t think it’s fair for me to ask for more.//After all, a long and happy life is all anyone wants, right?
Text.LocalizedString: Dad had a happy and long life. I don’t think it’s fair for me to ask for more.//After all, a long and happy life is all anyone wants, right?

Text.SourceString: Guess what I studied back in university?
Text.LocalizedString: Guess what I studied back in university?

Text.SourceString: Do I look artistic to you? That’s a huge compliment. Thank you. But, no, I studied accounting, actually.
Text.LocalizedString: Do I look artistic to you? That’s a huge compliment. Thank you. But, no, I studied accounting, actually.

Text.SourceString: How did you know? Did you study accounting too?
Text.LocalizedString: How did you know? Did you study accounting too?

Text.SourceString: No, I studied accounting. I wish I knew more about literature, though.
Text.LocalizedString: No, I studied accounting. I wish I knew more about literature, though.

Text.SourceString: I run a tavern and move around a lot. What am I supposed to wear, if not a polo shirt?
Text.LocalizedString: I run a tavern and move around a lot. What am I supposed to wear, if not a polo shirt?

Text.SourceString: I don’t want to look unprofessional, but I also don’t want to be uncomfortable.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t want to look unprofessional, but I also don’t want to be uncomfortable.

Text.SourceString: Growing up, Mama would always tell us red is a lucky color and to wear it on special occasions, like a wedding or New Year’s.//<portrait=happy>But we don’t always follow things like that to a T. <NpcName>Frank</> didn’t wear red at his wedding. No big deal!
Text.LocalizedString: Growing up, Mama would always tell us red is a lucky color and to wear it on special occasions, like a wedding or New Year’s.//<portrait=happy>But we don’t always follow things like that to a T. <NpcName>Frank</> didn’t wear red at his wedding. No big deal!

Text.SourceString: Mama's family is pretty strict about wearing red on New Year’s.//Whenever we celebrated with them, Ama, that's my grandma from Mama's side... She used to always dress us up in red. No exceptions!
Text.LocalizedString: Mama's family is pretty strict about wearing red on New Year’s.//Whenever we celebrated with them, Ama, that's my grandma from Mama's side... She used to always dress us up in red. No exceptions!

Text.SourceString: Dad’s side of the family doesn’t have that culture. We didn’t need to wear red with him…or Mama, actually.//She’s kind of modern that way.
Text.LocalizedString: Dad’s side of the family doesn’t have that culture. We didn’t need to wear red with him…or Mama, actually.//She’s kind of modern that way.

Text.SourceString: Back in my university days, my dorm was right next to a temple, and whenever Mama came to visit me, we’d go there and pray.//<portrait=happy>Mama would make sure we burned enough incense for our ancestors.
Text.LocalizedString: Back in my university days, my dorm was right next to a temple, and whenever Mama came to visit me, we’d go there and pray.//<portrait=happy>Mama would make sure we burned enough incense for our ancestors.

Text.SourceString: I remember smelling like ash for the rest of the day.//<portrait=normal>Here, we only pray at the house or at Dad’s grave.
Text.LocalizedString: I remember smelling like ash for the rest of the day.//<portrait=normal>Here, we only pray at the house or at Dad’s grave.

Text.SourceString: Have you done your farming for the day?
Text.LocalizedString: Have you done your farming for the day?

Text.SourceString: Oh, good!
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, good!

Text.SourceString: It’s almost the weekend.//<portrait=happy>But you already knew that.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s almost the weekend.//<portrait=happy>But you already knew that.

Text.SourceString: I was just thinking about checking up on you!
Text.LocalizedString: I was just thinking about checking up on you!

Text.SourceString: There are plenty of flowers around the lake.//<portrait=blushing>I had no idea you liked flowers. I would've picked some for you.
Text.LocalizedString: There are plenty of flowers around the lake.//<portrait=blushing>I had no idea you liked flowers. I would've picked some for you.

Text.SourceString: The cavern… Let’s talk about that. I think there’s more life in there than people think.//<portrait=surprised>Well, you’ve been inside, right? What do you think?
Text.LocalizedString: The cavern… Let’s talk about that. I think there’s more life in there than people think.//<portrait=surprised>Well, you’ve been inside, right? What do you think?

Text.SourceString: It’s really fun hanging out with you. Feel free to stop me if I monopolize the conversation too much, okay?
Text.LocalizedString: It’s really fun hanging out with you. Feel free to stop me if I monopolize the conversation too much, okay?

Text.SourceString: It’s hard for me to get a day off… Since, as you know, it’s just <NpcName>Frank</> and me at the Tavern.//<portrait=happy>But when I do, I’ll come by the farm and check up on you, okay?
Text.LocalizedString: It’s hard for me to get a day off… Since, as you know, it’s just <NpcName>Frank</> and me at the Tavern.//<portrait=happy>But when I do, I’ll come by the farm and check up on you, okay?

Text.SourceString: I like that you get along with my mom. It really shows what type of person you are…
Text.LocalizedString: I like that you get along with my mom. It really shows what type of person you are…

Text.SourceString: She’s been asking about us lately…errr, you, I guess. Asking about you in relation to me, to be specific.
Text.LocalizedString: She’s been asking about us lately…errr, you, I guess. Asking about you in relation to me, to be specific.

Text.SourceString: Here’s what I’m thinking: if the Tavern stays open longer, and we hire more people, I think both <NpcName>Frank</> and I will get more days off.//<portrait=happy>We’ll also make more money, on top of that.
Text.LocalizedString: Here’s what I’m thinking: if the Tavern stays open longer, and we hire more people, I think both <NpcName>Frank</> and I will get more days off.//<portrait=happy>We’ll also make more money, on top of that.

Text.SourceString: The tricky part is finding more people to train…and convincing <NpcName>Frank</> to spend more.//<portrait=annoyed>Good luck to me, I guess.
Text.LocalizedString: The tricky part is finding more people to train…and convincing <NpcName>Frank</> to spend more.//<portrait=annoyed>Good luck to me, I guess.

Text.SourceString: I’ve been watching too much TV lately. I need to get out more.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve been watching too much TV lately. I need to get out more.

Text.SourceString: Usually, when I get headaches like this, it’s because I need a new prescription for my glasses.
Text.LocalizedString: Usually, when I get headaches like this, it’s because I need a new prescription for my glasses.

Text.SourceString: Ugh… This can’t be good.
Text.LocalizedString: Ugh… This can’t be good.

Text.SourceString: Sometimes I think I should just give up trying to run the Tavern and let <NpcName>Frank</> take over.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes I think I should just give up trying to run the Tavern and let <NpcName>Frank</> take over.

Text.SourceString: But then I remember the Tavern is a legacy.//<portrait=normal>It was my parents’, and someday, <NpcName>Frank</> and I will pass it to the next generation.
Text.LocalizedString: But then I remember the Tavern is a legacy.//<portrait=normal>It was my parents’, and someday, <NpcName>Frank</> and I will pass it to the next generation.

Text.SourceString: Sometimes I wonder what my life would have been like if I’d stayed in Pokyo after university.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes I wonder what my life would have been like if I’d stayed in Pokyo after university.

Text.SourceString: But I am who I am. I’ve realized I like familiarity, and the familiarity I like the most is right here.
Text.LocalizedString: But I am who I am. I’ve realized I like familiarity, and the familiarity I like the most is right here.

Text.SourceString: Do I have cat hair on me?
Text.LocalizedString: Do I have cat hair on me?

Text.SourceString: I played with <NPCName>Peanut</> and <NPCName>Butter</> earlier, and there was a lot of hair on my shirt.//I think I got most of it off.
Text.LocalizedString: I played with <NPCName>Peanut</> and <NPCName>Butter</> earlier, and there was a lot of hair on my shirt.//I think I got most of it off.

Text.SourceString: Hey! So nice to run into you, <PlayerName>$player</>.
Text.LocalizedString: Hey! So nice to run into you, <PlayerName>$player</>.

Text.SourceString: I was a bit bored… But I feel better now, after talking to you.//<portrait=normal>Thanks for asking.
Text.LocalizedString: I was a bit bored… But I feel better now, after talking to you.//<portrait=normal>Thanks for asking.

Text.SourceString: Can you keep a secret?
Text.LocalizedString: Can you keep a secret?

Text.SourceString: There’s something about cats, isn’t there? It makes me feel special when my brother’s cats come to visit me.//<portrait=blushing>They really know how to steal my heart, those furballs.
Text.LocalizedString: There’s something about cats, isn’t there? It makes me feel special when my brother’s cats come to visit me.//<portrait=blushing>They really know how to steal my heart, those furballs.

Text.SourceString: I enjoyed having a picnic with you that time.//<portrait=normal>If I promise to make you something else besides fried eggs…could we do that again sometime?
Text.LocalizedString: I enjoyed having a picnic with you that time.//<portrait=normal>If I promise to make you something else besides fried eggs…could we do that again sometime?

Text.SourceString: No promises, though…about the eggs.//<portrait=happy>The picnic, yes, I promise!
Text.LocalizedString: No promises, though…about the eggs.//<portrait=happy>The picnic, yes, I promise!

Text.SourceString: I think at this point in our lives, you and I both know there’s more out there than just us living in this universe.
Text.LocalizedString: I think at this point in our lives, you and I both know there’s more out there than just us living in this universe.

Text.SourceString: I never really gave a lot of thought to having my own family.
Text.LocalizedString: I never really gave a lot of thought to having my own family.

Text.SourceString: Maybe when the right person comes along, I can start thinking about it.
Text.LocalizedString: Maybe when the right person comes along, I can start thinking about it.

Text.SourceString: The first thing I did after graduating was move back here.
Text.LocalizedString: The first thing I did after graduating was move back here.

Text.SourceString: I feel guilty for spending a lot of money on university and never actually using my degree to get one of those fancy jobs at a big firm.
Text.LocalizedString: I feel guilty for spending a lot of money on university and never actually using my degree to get one of those fancy jobs at a big firm.

Text.SourceString: I wonder if I should start learning how to cook fancy things, like lodeh or pumpkin pie.//Well, anything besides fried eggs, really.
Text.LocalizedString: I wonder if I should start learning how to cook fancy things, like lodeh or pumpkin pie.//Well, anything besides fried eggs, really.

Text.SourceString: Do you like people who can cook? Or no?//<portrait=sad>I can cook a little, by the way. I mean, I’m not too bad at it, if you’re into that sort of stuff. Um…
Text.LocalizedString: Do you like people who can cook? Or no?//<portrait=sad>I can cook a little, by the way. I mean, I’m not too bad at it, if you’re into that sort of stuff. Um…

Text.SourceString: That…errr…looks good on you…
Text.LocalizedString: That…errr…looks good on you…

Text.SourceString: Oh my! Good. That looks good on you. The shirt.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh my! Good. That looks good on you. The shirt.

Text.SourceString: I don’t know how I would have coped if you hadn’t been there that time when my mom fell.//I was such a wreck.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t know how I would have coped if you hadn’t been there that time when my mom fell.//I was such a wreck.

Text.SourceString: I’m glad to have someone like you in my life.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m glad to have someone like you in my life.

Text.SourceString: Would you like to have a big family, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: Would you like to have a big family, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: I think I would like that.
Text.LocalizedString: I think I would like that.

Special.SourceString: Depends. If it’s with you, then yes.
Special.LocalizedString: Depends. If it’s with you, then yes.

252.SpecialTag: Depends. If it’s with you, then yes.
252.Question: None

Text.SourceString: I think I get what you’re saying.
Text.LocalizedString: I think I get what you’re saying.

Special.SourceString: No. I like me and just me.
Special.LocalizedString: No. I like me and just me.

253.SpecialTag: No. I like me and just me.
253.Question: None

Text.SourceString: Yeah, questions like that always catch me off guard. I have no idea why I asked you that.
Text.LocalizedString: Yeah, questions like that always catch me off guard. I have no idea why I asked you that.

Text.SourceString: Do you hang out with anyone special on the weekends?
Text.LocalizedString: Do you hang out with anyone special on the weekends?

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Alice</> is a childhood friend. We both like talking about mysteries and picking each other’s brains.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Alice</> is a childhood friend. We both like talking about mysteries and picking each other’s brains.

Text.SourceString: There’s nothing going on between <NpcName>Alice</> and me.//We’re just friends. I love her like my own sister.
Text.LocalizedString: There’s nothing going on between <NpcName>Alice</> and me.//We’re just friends. I love her like my own sister.

Text.SourceString: It’s tough to concentrate with you around… You’re so distracting!
Text.LocalizedString: It’s tough to concentrate with you around… You’re so distracting!

Text.SourceString: No, no, don’t go. I meant it in a good way. I would rather be here than doing something else.
Text.LocalizedString: No, no, don’t go. I meant it in a good way. I would rather be here than doing something else.

Text.SourceString: Your cheeks are getting red. You need to warm up…
Text.LocalizedString: Your cheeks are getting red. You need to warm up…

Text.SourceString: I would offer to warm you up, but…I’m afraid you might say no.
Text.LocalizedString: I would offer to warm you up, but…I’m afraid you might say no.

Text.SourceString: I can’t believe they don’t have pineapples.//I specifically came here looking for them.
Text.LocalizedString: I can’t believe they don’t have pineapples.//I specifically came here looking for them.

Text.SourceString: They ran out of tea leaves.//<portrait=concerned>I guess we won’t be serving green tea at the Tavern tomorrow.
Text.LocalizedString: They ran out of tea leaves.//<portrait=concerned>I guess we won’t be serving green tea at the Tavern tomorrow.

Text.SourceString: Hmm…
Text.LocalizedString: Hmm…

Text.SourceString: Your farm is just over the creek, right?
Text.LocalizedString: Your farm is just over the creek, right?

Text.SourceString: We should have picnics here more often.//<portrait=blushing>Just you and me.
Text.LocalizedString: We should have picnics here more often.//<portrait=blushing>Just you and me.

Text.SourceString: I know I tend to complain a lot, but I really don’t mean it.//<portrait=concerned>I was just venting, you know?
Text.LocalizedString: I know I tend to complain a lot, but I really don’t mean it.//<portrait=concerned>I was just venting, you know?

Text.SourceString: Thank you for being such a great listener.//<portrait=happy>And an even better friend.
Text.LocalizedString: Thank you for being such a great listener.//<portrait=happy>And an even better friend.

Text.SourceString: What do you think?//<portrait=normal>Would I look all right with longer hair, or no?
Text.LocalizedString: What do you think?//<portrait=normal>Would I look all right with longer hair, or no?

Text.SourceString: I’m really looking forward to all the fun things I have planned for this Spring.//Everything’s gonna start to bloom soon!
Text.LocalizedString: I’m really looking forward to all the fun things I have planned for this Spring.//Everything’s gonna start to bloom soon!

Text.SourceString: One of the good things about Summer is the fact that you can wear colorful shirts.
Text.LocalizedString: One of the good things about Summer is the fact that you can wear colorful shirts.

Text.SourceString: I hope we don’t start getting half-naked customers, being near the beach and all.//<portrait=annoyed>The only place where it’s socially acceptable to wear a bathing suit and flip-flops all day is the beach, never the Tavern.
Text.LocalizedString: I hope we don’t start getting half-naked customers, being near the beach and all.//<portrait=annoyed>The only place where it’s socially acceptable to wear a bathing suit and flip-flops all day is the beach, never the Tavern.

Text.SourceString: I hate having to run the heater all the time. It’s so expensive, and it dries out the air at the Tavern.
Text.LocalizedString: I hate having to run the heater all the time. It’s so expensive, and it dries out the air at the Tavern.

Text.SourceString: I’m so glad Spring is here! The weather is finally starting to warm up.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m so glad Spring is here! The weather is finally starting to warm up.

Text.SourceString: I always feel like a weight has been lifted off my shoulders when Winter ends and Spring begins.//It’s safe for Mama to walk outside again. No more ice.
Text.LocalizedString: I always feel like a weight has been lifted off my shoulders when Winter ends and Spring begins.//It’s safe for Mama to walk outside again. No more ice.

Text.SourceString: I’m looking forward to going on long walks with my mom and enjoying the beautiful Fall scenery.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m looking forward to going on long walks with my mom and enjoying the beautiful Fall scenery.

Text.SourceString: I’m really enjoying the slower pace of life in Fall. It’s a nice change from the busy Summer.//<portrait=happy>The beach is peaceful again. Ha ha!
Text.LocalizedString: I’m really enjoying the slower pace of life in Fall. It’s a nice change from the busy Summer.//<portrait=happy>The beach is peaceful again. Ha ha!

Text.SourceString: My brother <NpcName>Frank</> hates durian, but I think he’s out of his mind.//It’s the best fruit ever.
Text.LocalizedString: My brother <NpcName>Frank</> hates durian, but I think he’s out of his mind.//It’s the best fruit ever.

Text.SourceString: I always try to add durian to the menu and always fail ’cause <NpcName>Frank</> removes it right away. Who made him the boss?//<portrait=normal>Think of all the desserts you can make from it! Oh, sounds so good!
Text.LocalizedString: I always try to add durian to the menu and always fail ’cause <NpcName>Frank</> removes it right away. Who made him the boss?//<portrait=normal>Think of all the desserts you can make from it! Oh, sounds so good!

Text.SourceString: I love the way durian smells. Some people say it smells bad, but I think it smells amazing.
Text.LocalizedString: I love the way durian smells. Some people say it smells bad, but I think it smells amazing.

Text.SourceString: We used to have more mirrors here, but since we took them out for Dad’s funeral, we’ve been kind of too lazy to put them back.
Text.LocalizedString: We used to have more mirrors here, but since we took them out for Dad’s funeral, we’ve been kind of too lazy to put them back.

Text.SourceString: Mama has this thing where we must remove all mirrors during the funeral of a family member.//Bad luck, she said.
Text.LocalizedString: Mama has this thing where we must remove all mirrors during the funeral of a family member.//Bad luck, she said.

Text.SourceString: Having eggs in the morning is like an instant pick-me-up. Gets the day going!
Text.LocalizedString: Having eggs in the morning is like an instant pick-me-up. Gets the day going!

Text.SourceString: Have you noticed how the stars seem brighter out here in Starlet Town?//Nothing like a clear night sky to remind you how grand the universe is.
Text.LocalizedString: Have you noticed how the stars seem brighter out here in Starlet Town?//Nothing like a clear night sky to remind you how grand the universe is.

Text.SourceString: Just the smell of freshly baked bread from the oven is enough to make my day! There's nothing quite like it.//<NPCName>Eva</> is quite a baker.
Text.LocalizedString: Just the smell of freshly baked bread from the oven is enough to make my day! There's nothing quite like it.//<NPCName>Eva</> is quite a baker.

Text.SourceString: Need to dig out my swimming trunks, seems like the weather's heating up.
Text.LocalizedString: Need to dig out my swimming trunks, seems like the weather's heating up.

Text.SourceString: I gotta hunt down my sweater, starting to feel a bit chilly out here.
Text.LocalizedString: I gotta hunt down my sweater, starting to feel a bit chilly out here.
